@startuml
title Bootstrap — from process start to terminal state

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

participant "Android\n(ProcessLifecycleOwner)" as Proc
participant "OnboardingPlanBootstrapper\n(:app, MainProcessLifecycleObserver)" as Boot
participant "UserStageStore\n(:app)" as USS
participant "LinearOnboardingPlanProvider\n(:app)" as PP
participant "LinearOnboardingOrchestrator\n(:onboarding-impl)" as Orch
participant "Host activity / VM\n(observer)" as Host
participant "OnboardingSkipper\n(:app)" as Skip

== Process start ==

Proc -> Boot : onCreate(owner)
note right of Boot
  Bootstrapper is contributed as a
  MainProcessLifecycleObserver multibinding
  in :app, scoped to AppScope.
end note
Boot -> Boot : appScope.launch { ... }

== Decide whether to start ==

Boot -> USS : isNewUser()
USS --> Boot : true / false

alt user is NEW
  Boot -> PP : buildMainPlan(\n  onCompleted = { userStageStore.stageCompleted(NEW) },\n  onSkipped = { onboardingSkipper.markOnboardingAsCompleted() })
  PP --> Boot : LinearOnboardingPlan(steps=[...], onCompleted, onSkipped)
  Boot -> Orch : startPlan(plan)
  note right of Orch
    Idempotent — no-op if state != NotStarted.
    Walks plan from step 0, skipping any
    whose precondition() returns false.
  end note
  Orch -> Orch : push frame, advance to\nfirst eligible step
  Orch --> Host : state = InProgress(plan, idx)

else user is past NEW
  Boot -> Boot : no-op (legacy CTA path handles\nthe rest via CtaViewModel)
end

== Event loop runs (see event-loop diagram) ==

note over Host, Orch
  Hosts collect orchestrator.state, render dialogs /
  drive actions, and forward user actions back as
  events via onEvent(...). See the event-loop and
  host-coordination diagrams for the inner cycle.
end note

== Terminal — main plan exhausts or AbortPlan ==

alt main plan exhausts (or side plan exhausts)
  Orch -> Orch : advanceTopFrame() →\nindex >= steps.size

  Orch -> USS : mainPlan.onCompleted()\n→ stageCompleted(AppStage.NEW)
  USS --> Orch : DAX_ONBOARDING (written)

  note right of Orch
    AppStage write is awaited **before** the
    terminal state is emitted, so any listener
    that routes off Completed observes the
    post-write stage value.
  end note

  Orch -> Orch : _state.value = Completed
  Orch --> Host : state = Completed

else any step returns AbortPlan
  Orch -> Orch : frameStack.clear()

  Orch -> Skip : mainPlan.onSkipped()\n→ markOnboardingAsCompleted()
  Skip -> USS : stageCompleted(DAX_ONBOARDING)\n+ hideTips=true, dismiss ADD_WIDGET
  Skip --> Orch : done

  Orch -> Orch : _state.value = Skipped
  Orch --> Host : state = Skipped
end

@enduml
